<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Small species, represented by four posteriorly incomplete specimens, 4-4.5 mm long and 0.4-0.7 mm wide. Holotype posteriorly incomplete, but otherwise in good condition, 4.5 mm long and 0.7 mm wide at the widest point for 18 chaetigers long fragment. Colour in alcohol creamy white, without body pigment (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 26" captionStartId="F26" captionText="Figure 26. Oligobregma tani sp. nov. holotype (specimen NHM _ 1454). A Lab image, whole specimen (pre-stain,) B Live image, whole specimen C Lab image, dorsal anterior, (stained, h = prostomial horns, pe = peristomial ring) D Lab image, lateral anterior, (stained, h = prostomial horns, pe = peristomial ring) E Lab image, ventral anterior, (stained, vm = ventral midline) F Lab image, mid-body parapodia (faded stain, dc = dorsal cirrus, vc = ventral cirrus, ip = interramal papilla) G Lab image, detail of dorsal cirrus, with no internal gland visible (dc = dorsal cirrus) H Lab image, detail of hirsute spines on notopodia on chaetiger 1 ([left panel]) I Lab image, detail of capillary and lyrate chaetae on chaetiger 12 J Lab image, detail lyrate chaetae. Morphological features in plates F, G have been outlined with a fine white line to improve clarity of those features. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A, C, E); 50 μm (G-I)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.883.36193.figure26" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/350278" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.883.36193.figure26">Fig. 26A</figureCitation>
); live specimens semi-translucent (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 26" captionStartId="F26" captionText="Figure 26. Oligobregma tani sp. nov. holotype (specimen NHM _ 1454). A Lab image, whole specimen (pre-stain,) B Live image, whole specimen C Lab image, dorsal anterior, (stained, h = prostomial horns, pe = peristomial ring) D Lab image, lateral anterior, (stained, h = prostomial horns, pe = peristomial ring) E Lab image, ventral anterior, (stained, vm = ventral midline) F Lab image, mid-body parapodia (faded stain, dc = dorsal cirrus, vc = ventral cirrus, ip = interramal papilla) G Lab image, detail of dorsal cirrus, with no internal gland visible (dc = dorsal cirrus) H Lab image, detail of hirsute spines on notopodia on chaetiger 1 ([left panel]) I Lab image, detail of capillary and lyrate chaetae on chaetiger 12 J Lab image, detail lyrate chaetae. Morphological features in plates F, G have been outlined with a fine white line to improve clarity of those features. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A, C, E); 50 μm (G-I)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.883.36193.figure26" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/350278" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.883.36193.figure26">Fig. 26B</figureCitation>
). Anterior body segments appears smooth, annulation of raised pads detected best upon staining (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 26" captionStartId="F26" captionText="Figure 26. Oligobregma tani sp. nov. holotype (specimen NHM _ 1454). A Lab image, whole specimen (pre-stain,) B Live image, whole specimen C Lab image, dorsal anterior, (stained, h = prostomial horns, pe = peristomial ring) D Lab image, lateral anterior, (stained, h = prostomial horns, pe = peristomial ring) E Lab image, ventral anterior, (stained, vm = ventral midline) F Lab image, mid-body parapodia (faded stain, dc = dorsal cirrus, vc = ventral cirrus, ip = interramal papilla) G Lab image, detail of dorsal cirrus, with no internal gland visible (dc = dorsal cirrus) H Lab image, detail of hirsute spines on notopodia on chaetiger 1 ([left panel]) I Lab image, detail of capillary and lyrate chaetae on chaetiger 12 J Lab image, detail lyrate chaetae. Morphological features in plates F, G have been outlined with a fine white line to improve clarity of those features. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A, C, E); 50 μm (G-I)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.883.36193.figure26" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/350278" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.883.36193.figure26">
Fig. 26
<normalizedToken originalValue="C–E">C-E</normalizedToken>
</figureCitation>
) revealing chaetigers 1-4 with two transverse rows of relatively large lobes; subsequent chaetigers may be tri-annulate, but epithelium with mostly with wrinkled appearance till end of fragment (chaetiger 18) (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 26" captionStartId="F26" captionText="Figure 26. Oligobregma tani sp. nov. holotype (specimen NHM _ 1454). A Lab image, whole specimen (pre-stain,) B Live image, whole specimen C Lab image, dorsal anterior, (stained, h = prostomial horns, pe = peristomial ring) D Lab image, lateral anterior, (stained, h = prostomial horns, pe = peristomial ring) E Lab image, ventral anterior, (stained, vm = ventral midline) F Lab image, mid-body parapodia (faded stain, dc = dorsal cirrus, vc = ventral cirrus, ip = interramal papilla) G Lab image, detail of dorsal cirrus, with no internal gland visible (dc = dorsal cirrus) H Lab image, detail of hirsute spines on notopodia on chaetiger 1 ([left panel]) I Lab image, detail of capillary and lyrate chaetae on chaetiger 12 J Lab image, detail lyrate chaetae. Morphological features in plates F, G have been outlined with a fine white line to improve clarity of those features. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A, C, E); 50 μm (G-I)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.883.36193.figure26" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/350278" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.883.36193.figure26">
Fig. 26
<normalizedToken originalValue="B–E">B-E</normalizedToken>
</figureCitation>
).Ventral midline on venter not too prominent, from chaetiger 2, composed of a row of large pads within a groove (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 26" captionStartId="F26" captionText="Figure 26. Oligobregma tani sp. nov. holotype (specimen NHM _ 1454). A Lab image, whole specimen (pre-stain,) B Live image, whole specimen C Lab image, dorsal anterior, (stained, h = prostomial horns, pe = peristomial ring) D Lab image, lateral anterior, (stained, h = prostomial horns, pe = peristomial ring) E Lab image, ventral anterior, (stained, vm = ventral midline) F Lab image, mid-body parapodia (faded stain, dc = dorsal cirrus, vc = ventral cirrus, ip = interramal papilla) G Lab image, detail of dorsal cirrus, with no internal gland visible (dc = dorsal cirrus) H Lab image, detail of hirsute spines on notopodia on chaetiger 1 ([left panel]) I Lab image, detail of capillary and lyrate chaetae on chaetiger 12 J Lab image, detail lyrate chaetae. Morphological features in plates F, G have been outlined with a fine white line to improve clarity of those features. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A, C, E); 50 μm (G-I)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.883.36193.figure26" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/350278" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.883.36193.figure26">Fig. 26E</figureCitation>
). Branchiae absent.
</paragraph>
